node.title: Protest camp springs up in Christchurch's Latimer Square
node.description: A protest camp has sprung up in Christchurch's Latimer Square, where signs and tents have been hammered into the grass.
node.content:
["A protest camp has sprung up in Christchurch's Latimer Square, where signs and tents have been hammered into the grass.", "", "
Photo: RNZ
", "There did not appear to be anyone in the tents early this morning.", "Some of the signs are about freedom fighting, while another says 'Occupy Christchurch'.", "The city council is monitoring the site.", "Elsewhere in the city, the council has told anti-mandate protesters camping on earthquake-damaged red-zone land elsewhere in the city to leave.", "The group has been there since the start of the month.", "Anti-mandate protesters occupied Cranmer Square for weeks, but left peacefully.", "", "
Photo: RNZ
"]
